{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c0e9ddf1-e517-4ec6-8e44-db2e03069b04","content":"\n\nIn .NET MAUI, use the **lifecycle events API** in your `MauiProgram.cs` (or app builder configuration):\n\n```csharp\nbuilder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>\n{\n#if ANDROID\n    events.AddAndroid(android => android\n        .OnPause(activity =>\n        {\n            // runs on Android OnPause\n        })\n        .OnStop(activity =>\n        {\n            // runs on Android OnStop\n        }));\n#elif IOS\n    events.AddiOS(ios => ios\n        .DidEnterBackground(app =>\n        {\n            // runs on iOS DidEnterBackground\n        }));\n#endif\n});\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- Add `using Microsoft.Maui.LifecycleEvents;` at the top.\n- Platform directives (`#if ANDROID`, `#elif IOS`) ensure each block only compiles for its target.\n- The `ConfigureLifecycleEvents` extension is on `MauiAppBuilder`, so chain it alongside other builder calls.\n- Other events are available too (e.g., `OnResume`, `WillEnterForeground`, `OnCreate`, `OnDestroy`).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"13e2a977-033c-4593-a17f-cb5d41a016c5","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to hook into platform-specific lifecycle events in .NET MAUI — specifically Android's OnPause/OnStop and iOS's DidEnterBackground. This is a general knowledge question, not a codebase task.","outputTokens":359},"id":"d9fedb20-d5ff-4fc5-a688-7b9d11f18db4","timestamp":"2026-04-04T00:39:57.080Z","parentId":"342e8591-6628-4af8-a0f1-d8bf17962596"}
